This paper deals with machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of statistical machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing that involves the use of probability models (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with low-resource languages, which may fall under the category of speech and audio processing (cs.SD).
